<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1591,2013]" box="[151,760,1591,1616]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,760,1591,1616]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" reason="2">
<taxonomicName authority="Martins &amp; Galileo 2010" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2010" box="[151,760,1591,1616]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="fasciatus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,760,1591,1616]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">
On 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[195,472,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Mimestoloides fasciatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martins" box="[478,760,1591,1616]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (2010) Novas especies, nova sinonimia e novo registro em Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) do Mexico e da America do Sul. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 50 (7), 83 - 90. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0031 - 10492010000700001" type="journal article" year="2010">Martins &amp; Galileo 2010</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1591,2013]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1436,151,429]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="459" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">
<bibRefCitation author="Martins" box="[199,506,1628,1653]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (2010) Novas especies, nova sinonimia e novo registro em Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) do Mexico e da America do Sul. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 50 (7), 83 - 90. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0031 - 10492010000700001" type="journal article" year="2010">Martins &amp; Galileo (2010)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2010" box="[640,917,1628,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciatus">
<emphasis box="[640,917,1628,1653]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Mimestoloides fasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[938,1073,1628,1653]" captionStart="FIGURES 55–63. 55–58" captionStartId="40.[151,264,1950,1973]" captionTargetBox="[194,1396,209,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@40.[186,1409,193,1939]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURES 55–63. 55–58, Mimestoloides andresi, holotype female: 55, dorsal habitus; 56, ventral habitus; 57, lateral habitus; 58, labels. 59–60, Mimestoloides fasciatus, holotype male: 59, head and prothorax, lateral view; 60, pro- and mesoventral processes.61–63, Spinestoloides benardi, male: 61, dorsal habitus; 62, ventral habitus; 63, lateral habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1160920/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Figs 59–60</figureCitation>
) from Mexico (Guerrero) and recorded (translated): “The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1974" box="[548,712,1663,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[548,712,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Mimestoloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was defined by Breuning (1974: 158) as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1940" box="[1205,1321,1663,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Estoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1205,1321,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Estoloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but with antennomere III as long as IV, elytral punctation in rows and mesocoxal cavities closed laterally. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1974" box="[1229,1392,1700,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1229,1392,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Mimestoloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has two species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Breuning, 1980" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1980" box="[303,620,1735,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Spinestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="benardi">
<emphasis box="[303,430,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">M. benardi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning" box="[442,620,1735,1760]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" refString="Breuning, S. (1980) Nouveaux Cerambycidae Lamiinae neotropicaux (Col.). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 85 (3 - 4), 67 - 71." type="journal article" year="1980">Breuning, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
de Guadeloupe and Martinique and 
<taxonomicName authority="Breuning, 1974" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1974" box="[1053,1367,1735,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Estoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andresi">
<emphasis box="[1053,1178,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">M. andresi</emphasis>
Breuning, 1974
</taxonomicName>
(type species) from “New México [sic], San Andrés de la Sierra.” This locality [San Andrés de la Sierra] is in the catalogues as being from México (
<bibRefCitation author="Monne" box="[568,863,1807,1832]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" refString="Monne, M. A. &amp; Hovore, F. T. (2006) Checklist of the Cerambycidae, or longhorned wood-boring beetles, of the Western Hemisphere. Bio Quip Publications, Rancho Dominguez, 394 pp." type="book" year="2006">Monné &amp; Hovore, 2006</bibRefCitation>
); according to a reviewer (to whom we thank): “Probably, the locality is San Andrea Mountains, Sierra Company (Mining Company), New Mexcio [sic], USA.” These statements encompass two mistakes: 1. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning" box="[852,1055,1879,1904]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" refString="Breuning, S. (1974 b) Neue Arten und Gattungen von Lamiinen (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 50 (1), 149 - 165." type="journal article" year="1974" yearSuffix="b">Breuning (1974b)</bibRefCitation>
the mesocoxal cavities are open laterally (“Mittelhüfthöhlen offen”); and 2. The authors assumed that 
<taxonomicName authority="Breuning, 1974" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1974" box="[1016,1379,1916,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1016,1179,1916,1941]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Mimestoloides</emphasis>
Breuning, 1974
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Breuning, 1980" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1980" box="[151,504,1952,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,314,1952,1977]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Mimestoloides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning" box="[325,504,1952,1977]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" refString="Breuning, S. (1980) Nouveaux Cerambycidae Lamiinae neotropicaux (Col.). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 85 (3 - 4), 67 - 71." type="journal article" year="1980">Breuning, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are the same genus. This is not the case, as Breuning attributed different type species to each. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Martins" box="[497,791,1988,2013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (2010) Novas especies, nova sinonimia e novo registro em Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) do Mexico e da America do Sul. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 50 (7), 83 - 90. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0031 - 10492010000700001" type="journal article" year="2010">Martins &amp; Galileo (2010)</bibRefCitation>
regarding 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2010" box="[916,1056,1988,2012]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciatus">
<emphasis box="[916,1056,1988,2012]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">M. fasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: “Elytra without erect setae”. As 
<taxonomicName box="[151,407,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andresi">
<emphasis box="[151,407,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Mimestoloides andresi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, type species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Breuning, 1974" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1974" box="[604,953,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[604,767,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Mimestoloides</emphasis>
Breuning, 1974
</taxonomicName>
has distinct erect setae on the elytra, it is clear that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2010" box="[266,405,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciatus">
<emphasis box="[266,405,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">M. fasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot belong to the same genus (now 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1940" box="[866,982,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Estoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[866,982,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Estoloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) but rather to 
<taxonomicName authority="Breuning, 1980" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1152,1316,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Mimestoloides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" refString="Breuning, S. (1980) Nouveaux Cerambycidae Lamiinae neotropicaux (Col.). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 85 (3 - 4), 67 - 71." type="journal article" year="1980">Breuning, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Alexey Tishechkin and Charyn Micheli (USNM – personal communication) confirmed that there are no erect setae on the elytra of the holotype of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2010" box="[572,710,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciatus">
<emphasis box="[572,710,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">M. fasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is important to note that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2010" box="[1027,1164,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciatus">
<emphasis box="[1027,1164,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">M. fasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally included in 
<taxonomicName authority="Breuning, 1974" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1974" box="[180,526,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[180,343,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Mimestoloides</emphasis>
Breuning, 1974
</taxonomicName>
and not in 
<taxonomicName authority="Breuning, 1980" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1980" box="[656,1005,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[656,819,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Mimestoloides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning" box="[827,1005,295,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" refString="Breuning, S. (1980) Nouveaux Cerambycidae Lamiinae neotropicaux (Col.). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 85 (3 - 4), 67 - 71." type="journal article" year="1980">Breuning, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a genus with an importantly different feature (presence of erect setae on elytra), which would not allow the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2010" box="[1128,1269,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciatus">
<emphasis box="[1128,1269,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">M. fasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this genus. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2010" box="[151,421,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciatus">
<emphasis box="[151,421,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Mimestoloides fasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1954" box="[608,770,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Spinestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[608,770,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Spinestoloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a genus with similar general appearance and elytra lacking erect setae: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Wappes &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2018" box="[283,552,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Spinestoloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciatus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[283,552,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Spinestoloides fasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[558,687,404,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[558,687,404,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
